cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use AUGMANITAI in your research, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
title: "AUGMANITAI: 1000-Term Compendium"
abstract: >-
  AUGMANITAI is a curated terminology for phenomena at the human–AI interface,
  published as a priority-establishing terminological deposit. The core deliverable
  is the 1000-Term Compendium, formalized as an RDF knowledge graph informed by
  ISO 704 / ISO 1087 / ISO 30042 (ISO-inspired, not ISO-certified) and serialized
  with W3C SKOS, SKOS-XL, OntoLex-Lemon, SHACL, and JSON-LD. The compendium is the
  curated output of a longitudinal n=1 observation of daily human–LLM interaction
  over approximately nine months and is offered as descriptive linguistic research
  (non-peer-reviewed). The priority claim covers the schema as a whole — its
  selection, definition, relation structure, and serialization — not the invention
  of each individual term; some terms are imported from prior literature, some
  are re-formulations, and some are newly introduced where no existing label fit.
  See DISCLAIMER.md (§1–§20) and METHODOLOGY.md (§2.0, §3, §11) in the repository
  for the study design, origin categories, and restricted-application clause (§20).
authors:
